title: Linking Social Stressors and Health System Gaps in Madison County, Kentucky
author: Author A. B.
summary: This paper examines how structural determinants such as education, food insecurity, and employment influence public health challenges in Madison County, Kentucky. The study evaluates both clinical outcomes and barriers to care among low-income groups.

statistical_analysis.findings: Among residents of Madison County, Kentucky, food insecurity and unemployment were associated with increased rates of untreated chronic illness and hospital readmissions (p < 0.01). Counties with targeted community-based interventions saw modest improvement over time.

policy_implication: Suggested actions for Madison County, Kentucky include strengthening food assistance programs, expanding public transit to medical facilities, and introducing community health worker programs in underserved zones.
references: Madison County, Kentucky Department of Public Health Report
